# create list for tweet json data
tweet_json = []

# iterate through tweet ids to retrieve tweets as json objects:
for tweet in tweet_ids:
    # use try/except for missing tweet ids
    try:
        tweet = api.get_status(tweet)
        tweet_json.append(tweet._json)
    except:
        continue

Assessing Data¶

In this section, detect and document at least eight (8) quality issues and two (2) tidiness issue. You must use both visual assessment programmatic assessement to assess the data.

Note: pay attention to the following key points when you access the data.

  • You only want original ratings (no retweets) that have images. Though there are 5000+ tweets in the dataset, not all are dog ratings and some are retweets.
  • Assessing and cleaning the entire dataset completely would require a lot of time, and is not necessary to practice and demonstrate your skills in data wrangling. Therefore, the requirements of this project are only to assess and clean at least 8 quality issues and at least 2 tidiness issues in this dataset.
  • The fact that the rating numerators are greater than the denominators does not need to be cleaned. This unique rating system is a big part of the popularity of WeRateDogs.
  • You do not need to gather the tweets beyond August 1st, 2017. You can, but note that you won't be able to gather the image predictions for these tweets since you don't have access to the algorithm used.

Quality¶

twitter_archive_enhanced table¶
  • Some tweets are retweets
  • Some tweets are replies
  • Some observations are missing URLs
  • Timestamp column is in string datatype
image_pred table¶
  • Consistency issues with breed names in columns "p1", "p2", "p3". Capitalization, hyphens, and dashes for spaces
tweets table¶
  • created_at column in string format
  • many columns with null values or very few non-nulls
  • duplicated images exist, however this does not affect the analysis

Tidiness issues¶

  • Merge tables into master dataframe and any remaining entries without retweet, favorite count, and images should be dropped
twitter_archive_enhanced table¶
  • Columns doggo, floofer, pupper, puppo are variables of dog stage and belong in a single column. Some dogs have multiple stages.

Cleaning Data¶

In this section, clean all of the issues you documented while assessing.

Define¶

Issue #2: Data Inconsistency¶

predict_clean: Consistency issues with breed names in columns "p1", "p2", "p3". Capitalization, hyphens, and dashes for spaces.

Define¶

Update p1, p2, p3 columns to title case, replace -'s and _'s with spaces

Code¶

In [50]:
# update p1, p2, p3 column values so all dog breeds are consistently capitalized and spaced
columns = ['p1', 'p2', 'p3']

for column in columns:
    predict_clean[column] = predict_clean[column].str.replace("_", " ")
    predict_clean[column] = predict_clean[column].str.replace("-", " ")
    predict_clean[column] = predict_clean[column].str.title()
